==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Humin
<hw>Hu"min</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>humus</ets>
the earth, ground.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A bitter, brownish
yellow, amorphous substance, extracted from vegetable mold, and also
produced by the action of acids on certain sugars and carbohydrates; --
called also <altname>humic acid</altname>, <altname>ulmin</altname>,
<altname>gein</altname>, <altname>ulmic</altname> or <altname>geic
acid</altname>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Humiri</ent>⟦br⟧
